Project title: Heart
  Purpose of this project: It represent love, emotion, and feelings. People often use heart to express affection, care, and deep connection with others
    How to run your code: Step 1: Install Python
1. Go to python.org.
2. Download and install Python. Make sure to check the box that says "Add Python to PATH" during installation.
Step 2: Save Your Code
1. Open Notepad or any text editor.
2. Copy your code and paste it into the text editor.
3. Save the file with a name like draw_pattern.py.
Step 3: Run the Code
1. Open Command Prompt (on Windows) or Terminal (on Mac).
2. Go to the folder where your draw_pattern.py file is saved. For example, type this in the terminal:
cd path\to\your\file
3. Type the following and press Enter:
python draw_pattern.py
(On Mac/Linux, you might need to type python3 instead of python).
Step 4: See the Result
A new window will pop up showing the drawing being created with colors.
Done! The turtle graphics window will appear, and the pattern will be drawn.
